```python
def check_permission(user, resource, action):
    if user.level >= 100:
        return True
    if action in ("view", "edit", "delete") and (resource.is_public or user.user_id == resource.owner_id):
        return True
    return False
```
This version allows any action (view, edit, delete) if the resource is public or owned by the user, regardless of their specific level, as long as they aren't an admin. It passes all your new tests for managers and generic users.
